Structs/Request.html#/s:7JsonRPC7Request.name: method
Structs/Request.html#/s:7JsonRPC7Request.abstract: A String containing the name of the method to be invoked. Method names that begin with the word rpc followed by a period character (U+002E or ASCII 46) are reserved for rpc-internal methods and extensions and MUST NOT be used for anything else.

Structs/Request.html#/s:7JsonRPC7Request.name: id
Structs/Request.html#/s:7JsonRPC7Request.abstract: An identifier established by the Client that MUST contain a String, Number, or NULL value if included.

Structs/Request.html#/s:7JsonRPC7Request.name: params
Structs/Request.html#/s:7JsonRPC7Request.abstract: A Structured value that holds the parameter values to be used during the invocation of the method. This member MAY be omitted.

Enums/Response.html#/s:7JsonRPC8Response.name: error
Enums/Response.html#/s:7JsonRPC8Response.abstract: Error response: when a rpc call encounters an error, the ErrorObject must contain the error member with a value.

Enums/Response.html#/s:7JsonRPC8Response.name: id
Enums/Response.html#/s:7JsonRPC8Response.abstract: It must be the same as the value of the id member in the Request Object.

Enums/Id.html#/s:7JsonRPC2IdO2eeoiSbAC_A.abstract: Returns a Boolean value indicating whether two Id are equal.

Enums/ErrorObject.html#/s:7JsonRPC11Erro.name: parseError
Enums/ErrorObject.html#/s:7JsonRPC11Erro.abstract: Invalid JSON was received by the server. An error occurred on the server while parsing the JSON text.

Enums/ErrorObject.html#/s:7JsonRPC11Erro.name: invalidRequest
Enums/ErrorObject.html#/s:7JsonRPC11Erro.abstract: The JSON sent is not a valid Request object.

Enums/ErrorObject.html#/s:7JsonRPC11Erro.name: methodNotFound
Enums/ErrorObject.html#/s:7JsonRPC11Erro.abstract: The method does not exist / is not available.

Enums/ErrorObject.html#/s:7JsonRPC11Erro.name: code
Enums/ErrorObject.html#/s:7JsonRPC11Erro.abstract: A Number that indicates the error type that occurred.

Enums/ErrorObject.html#/s:7JsonRPC11Erro.name: message
Enums/ErrorObject.html#/s:7JsonRPC11Erro.abstract: A String providing a short description of the error.

Enums/ErrorObject.html#/s:7JsonRPC11Erro.name: data
Enums/ErrorObject.html#/s:7JsonRPC11Erro.abstract: A Primitive or Structured value that contains additional information about the error.

Enums/ErrorObject.html#/s:7JsonRPC11Erro.name: isValidImplementationDefinedCode(_:)
Enums/ErrorObject.html#/s:7JsonRPC11Erro.abstract: Returns true if the code is defined in the range for the implementation-defined server-errors.

Enums/ErrorObject.html.name: ErrorObject
Enums/ErrorObject.html.abstract: When a rpc call encounters an error, the Response Object MUST contain the error member

Enums/Response.html.name: Response
Enums/Response.html.abstract: When a rpc call is made, the Server must reply with a Response, except for in the case of Notifications.
